{"title_page": "Ceylin del Carmen Alvarado", "text_new": "{{short description|Dutch cyclist}}\n{{spanish name 2|del Carmen|Alvarado}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Ceylin del Carmen Alvarado\n| image          = 2019 Citadelcross Namur podium7a.jpg\n| caption        = Del Carmen Alvarado in 2019\n| fullname       = Ceylin del Carmen Alvarado\n| nickname       =\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1998|8|6}}\n| birth_place    = [[Cabrera, Mar\u00eda Trinidad S\u00e1nchez|Cabrera]], [[Dominican Republic]]\n| height         =\n| weight         =\n| currentteam    = {{ubl|{{ct|COC}} ''(cyclo-cross)''|{{ct|CIM}} ''(road)''}}\n| discipline     = {{ubl|Cyclo-cross|Road}}\n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      =\n| amateuryears1  =\n| amateurteam1   = \n| proyears1      = 2019\u2013\n| proteam1       = {{ct|COC|2019}}\n| proyears2      = 2020\u2013\n| proteam2       = {{ct|CIM|2020}} ''(road)''\n| majorwins      = ;Cyclo-cross\n:[[UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|World Championships]] ([[2020 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|2020]])\n:[[Dutch National Cyclo-cross Championships|National Championships]] (2020)\n| medaltemplates =\n{{MedalCountry| {{NED}} }}\n{{MedalSport| Women's [[cyclo-cross]] }}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|World Championships]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2020 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|2020 D\u00fcbendorf]]|[[2020 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships \u2013 Women's elite race|Elite]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2018 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|2018 Valkenburg]]|Under-23}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2019 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|2019 Bogense]]|Under-23}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[UEC European Cyclo-cross Championships]]}}\n{{MedalGold |[[UEC European Cyclo-cross Championships|2018 Rosmalen]]|Under-23 race}}\n{{MedalGold |[[UEC European Cyclo-cross Championships|2019 Silvelle]]|Under-23 race}}\n}}\n'''Ceylin del Carmen Alvarado''' (born 6 August 1998) is a [[Dominican Republic|Dominican]]-born [[Netherlands|Dutch]] cyclist, who currently competes in [[cyclo-cross]] for UCI Cyclo-cross team {{ct|COC}},<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uci.org/cyclo-cross/teams/TeamDetail/14048/1002978/268|title=Alpecin - Fenix|work=UCI.org|publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|accessdate=25 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200425131316/https://www.uci.org/cyclo-cross/teams/TeamDetail/14048/1002978/268|archivedate=25 April 2020}}</ref> and in road cycling for [[UCI Women's Team|UCI Women's Continental team]] {{ct|CIM}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uci.org/road/teams/TeamDetail/15079/2003484/258|title=Ciclismo Mundial|work=UCI.org|publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|accessdate=25 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200425132540/https://www.uci.org/road/teams/TeamDetail/15079/2003484/258|archivedate=25 April 2020}}</ref> In 2018, she won the gold medal in the Under-23 race at the [[UEC European Cyclo-cross Championships]] in [[Rosmalen]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cyclingnews.com/races/uec-cyclo-cross-european-championships-2018/under-23-women/results/|title=Del Carmen Alvarado wins under 23 women's European cyclo-cross crown|publisher=[[cyclingnews.com]]|date=4 November 2018|accessdate=9 October 2019}}</ref> She repeated this feat in 2019. On 1 February 2020 she became world champion in the elite category at the [[2020 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships]] in [[D\u00fcbendorf, Switzerland]].\n\n==Major results==\n{{div col|colwidth=25em}}\n;2015\u20132016\n: 2nd [[Dutch National Cyclo-cross Championships|National Under-23 Championships]]\n;2016\u20132017\n: Qiansen Trophy\n::1st Fengtai Station\n::1st Yanqing Station\n;2017\u20132018\n: 2nd [[File:Silver medal blank.svg|15px]] [[2018 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|UCI World Under-23 Championships]]\n: Soudal Classics\n::3rd [[Grand Prix van Hasselt]]\n::3rd [[Cyclocross Leuven]]\n: [[2017\u201318 Brico Cross Trophy|Brico Cross]]\n::3rd [[Vestingcross]]\n: 3rd Kiremko Nacht van Woerden\n;2018\u20132019\n: 1st [[File:EuropeanChampionJersey(2016).png|20px]] [[UEC European Cyclo-cross Championships|UEC European Under-23 Championships]]\n: 1st [[File:MaillotHolanda.svg|20px]] [[Dutch National Cyclo-cross Championships|National Under-23 Championships]]\n: 1st [[File:Jersey white.svg|20px]] Overall [[2018\u201319 UCI Cyclo-cross World Cup|Under-23 UCI World Cup]]\n: 1st Overall [[2018\u201319 Cyclo-cross Superprestige|Under-23 Superprestige]]\n: [[DVV Trophy]]\n::1st [[Brussels Universities Cross]]\n: [[2018\u201319 Cyclo-cross Superprestige|Superprestige]]\n::2nd [[Noordzeecross]]\n::3rd [[Cyclo-cross Zonhoven]]\n: 2nd [[Grand Prix Neerpelt]]\n: 3rd [[File:Bronze medal blank.svg|15px]] [[2019 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|UCI World Under-23 Championships]]\n: [[Brico Cross]]\n::3rd Geraardsbergen\n: 3rd [[Nationale Cyclo-Cross Otegem]]\n;2019\u20132020\n: 1st [[File:Jersey rainbow.svg|20px]] [[2020 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|UCI World Championships]]\n: 1st [[File:MaillotHolanda.svg|20px]] [[Dutch National Cyclo-cross Championships|National Championships]]\n: 1st [[File:EuropeanChampionJersey(2016).png|20px]] [[UEC European Cyclo-cross Championships|UEC European Under-23 Championships]]\n: 1st Overall [[DVV Trophy]]\n::1st [[GP Mario De Clercq]]\n::1st [[Azencross]]\n::1st [[Grand Prix Sven Nys]]\n::1st [[Brussels Universities Cross]]\n::1st [[Krawatencross]]\n: 1st Overall [[2019\u201320 Cyclo-cross Superprestige|Superprestige]]\n::1st [[Superprestige Gieten]]\n::1st [[Cyclo-cross Ruddervoorde]]\n::1st [[Noordzeecross]]\n::2nd [[Cyclo-cross Zonhoven]]\n::2nd [[Superprestige Diegem]]\n::3rd [[Cyclo-cross Gavere]]\n: 2nd Overall [[2019\u201320 UCI Cyclo-cross World Cup|UCI World Cup]]\n::1st [[File:Jersey white.svg|20px]] Under-23 classification\n::1st [[Duinencross Koksijde]]\n::2nd [[Cyclo-cross Namur]]\n::2nd [[Grand Prix Erik De Vlaeminck]]\n::2nd [[Grand Prix Nommay]]\n: [[Ethias Cross]]\n::1st [[Berencross]]\n::1st [[Vestingcross]]\n::3rd [[Polderscross]]\n: 1st [[Grand Prix Neerpelt]]\n: 1st Cyclocross Gullegem\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cycling archives|119340}}\n*{{Procyclingstats|ceylin-del-carmen-alvarado}}\n\n{{UCI Cyclo-cross World Champions \u2013 Women's elite race}}\n{{Ciclismo Mundial riders}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Alvarado, Ceylin del Carmen}}\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Dutch female cyclists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Dutch cyclist}}\n{{spanish name 2|del Carmen|Alvarado}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Ceylin del Carmen Alvarado\n| image          = 2019 Citadelcross Namur podium7a.jpg\n| caption        = Del Carmen Alvarado in 2019\n| fullname       = Ceylin del Carmen Alvarado\n| nickname       =\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1998|8|6}}\n| birth_place    = [[Cabrera, Mar\u00eda Trinidad S\u00e1nchez|Cabrera]], [[Dominican Republic]]\n| height         =\n| weight         = \n| currentteam    = {{ubl|{{ct|COC}} ''(cyclo-cross)''|{{ct|CIM}} ''(road)''}}\n| discipline     = {{ubl|Cyclo-cross|Road}}\n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      =\n| amateuryears1  =\n| amateurteam1   = \n| proyears1      = 2019\u2013\n| proteam1       = {{ct|COC|2019}}\n| proyears2      = 2020\u2013\n| proteam2       = {{ct|CIM|2020}} ''(road)''\n| majorwins      = ;Cyclo-cross\n:[[UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|World Championships]] ([[2020 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|2020]])\n:[[Dutch National Cyclo-cross Championships|National Championships]] (2020)\n| medaltemplates =\n{{MedalCountry| {{NED}} }}\n{{MedalSport| Women's [[cyclo-cross]] }}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|World Championships]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2020 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|2020 D\u00fcbendorf]]|[[2020 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships \u2013 Women's elite race|Elite]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2018 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|2018 Valkenburg]]|Under-23}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2019 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|2019 Bogense]]|Under-23}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[UEC European Cyclo-cross Championships]]}}\n{{MedalGold |[[UEC European Cyclo-cross Championships|2018 Rosmalen]]|Under-23 race}}\n{{MedalGold |[[UEC European Cyclo-cross Championships|2019 Silvelle]]|Under-23 race}}\n}}\n'''Ceylin del Carmen Alvarado''' (born 6 August 1998) is a [[Dominican Republic|Dominican]]-born [[Netherlands|Dutch]] cyclist who competes in [[cyclo-cross]] for UCI Cyclo-cross team {{ct|COC}},<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uci.org/cyclo-cross/teams/TeamDetail/14048/1002978/268|title=Alpecin - Fenix|work=UCI.org|publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|accessdate=25 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200425131316/https://www.uci.org/cyclo-cross/teams/TeamDetail/14048/1002978/268|archivedate=25 April 2020}}</ref> and in road cycling for [[UCI Women's Team|UCI Women's Continental team]] {{ct|CIM}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uci.org/road/teams/TeamDetail/15079/2003484/258|title=Ciclismo Mundial|work=UCI.org|publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|accessdate=25 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200425132540/https://www.uci.org/road/teams/TeamDetail/15079/2003484/258|archivedate=25 April 2020}}</ref> In 2018, she won the gold medal in the Under-23 race at the [[UEC European Cyclo-cross Championships]] in [[Rosmalen]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cyclingnews.com/races/uec-cyclo-cross-european-championships-2018/under-23-women/results/|title=Del Carmen Alvarado wins under 23 women's European cyclo-cross crown|publisher=[[cyclingnews.com]]|date=4 November 2018|accessdate=9 October 2019}}</ref> She repeated this feat in 2019. On 1 February 2020 she became world champion in the elite category at the [[2020 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships]] in [[D\u00fcbendorf, Switzerland]].\n\n==Major results==\n{{div col|colwidth=25em}}\n;2015\u20132016\n: 2nd [[Dutch National Cyclo-cross Championships|National Under-23 Championships]]\n;2016\u20132017\n: Qiansen Trophy\n::1st Fengtai Station\n::1st Yanqing Station\n;2017\u20132018\n: 2nd [[File:Silver medal blank.svg|15px]] [[2018 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|UCI World Under-23 Championships]]\n: Soudal Classics\n::3rd [[Grand Prix van Hasselt]]\n::3rd [[Cyclocross Leuven]]\n: [[2017\u201318 Brico Cross Trophy|Brico Cross]]\n::3rd [[Vestingcross]]\n: 3rd Kiremko Nacht van Woerden\n;2018\u20132019\n: 1st [[File:EuropeanChampionJersey(2016).png|20px]] [[UEC European Cyclo-cross Championships|UEC European Under-23 Championships]]\n: 1st [[File:MaillotHolanda.svg|20px]] [[Dutch National Cyclo-cross Championships|National Under-23 Championships]]\n: 1st [[File:Jersey white.svg|20px]] Overall [[2018\u201319 UCI Cyclo-cross World Cup|Under-23 UCI World Cup]]\n: 1st Overall [[2018\u201319 Cyclo-cross Superprestige|Under-23 Superprestige]]\n: [[DVV Trophy]]\n::1st [[Brussels Universities Cross]]\n: [[2018\u201319 Cyclo-cross Superprestige|Superprestige]]\n::2nd [[Noordzeecross]]\n::3rd [[Cyclo-cross Zonhoven]]\n: 2nd [[Grand Prix Neerpelt]]\n: 3rd [[File:Bronze medal blank.svg|15px]] [[2019 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|UCI World Under-23 Championships]]\n: [[Brico Cross]]\n::3rd Geraardsbergen\n: 3rd [[Nationale Cyclo-Cross Otegem]]\n;2019\u20132020\n: 1st [[File:Jersey rainbow.svg|20px]] [[2020 UCI Cyclo-cross World Championships|UCI World Championships]]\n: 1st [[File:MaillotHolanda.svg|20px]] [[Dutch National Cyclo-cross Championships|National Championships]]\n: 1st [[File:EuropeanChampionJersey(2016).png|20px]] [[UEC European Cyclo-cross Championships|UEC European Under-23 Championships]]\n: 1st Overall [[DVV Trophy]]\n::1st [[GP Mario De Clercq]]\n::1st [[Azencross]]\n::1st [[Grand Prix Sven Nys]]\n::1st [[Brussels Universities Cross]]\n::1st [[Krawatencross]]\n: 1st Overall [[2019\u201320 Cyclo-cross Superprestige|Superprestige]]\n::1st [[Superprestige Gieten]]\n::1st [[Cyclo-cross Ruddervoorde]]\n::1st [[Noordzeecross]]\n::2nd [[Cyclo-cross Zonhoven]]\n::2nd [[Superprestige Diegem]]\n::3rd [[Cyclo-cross Gavere]]\n: 2nd Overall [[2019\u201320 UCI Cyclo-cross World Cup|UCI World Cup]]\n::1st [[File:Jersey white.svg|20px]] Under-23 classification\n::1st [[Duinencross Koksijde]]\n::2nd [[Cyclo-cross Namur]]\n::2nd [[Grand Prix Erik De Vlaeminck]]\n::2nd [[Grand Prix Nommay]]\n: [[Ethias Cross]]\n::1st [[Berencross]]\n::1st [[Vestingcross]]\n::3rd [[Polderscross]]\n: 1st [[Grand Prix Neerpelt]]\n: 1st Cyclocross Gullegem\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cycling archives|119340}}\n*{{Procyclingstats|ceylin-del-carmen-alvarado}}\n\n{{UCI Cyclo-cross World Champions \u2013 Women's elite race}}\n{{Ciclismo Mundial riders}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Alvarado, Ceylin del Carmen}}\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Dutch female cyclists]]\n", "name_user": "Cs-wolves", "label": "safe", "comment": "fix.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ceylin_del_Carmen_Alvarado"}
